'''Abdulelah Ali Awadh Al-Amri''' ({{langx|ar|عَبْد الْإِلَه عَلِيّ عَوَض الْعُمَرِيّ}}; born 15 January 1997) is a Saudi Arabian professional [[Association football|footballer]] who plays as a [[centre-back]] for [[Saudi Pro League]] club [[Al-Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]] and the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]].<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kooora.com/?cz=15887&player=126299|title=Abdullelah Ali Al Amri - Abdulelah Ali Alamri|website=Kooora|access-date=27 December 2018}}</ref>

==Club career==
Al-Amri progressed through [[Al Nassr FC|Al-Nassr]]'s youth system. He signed his first professional contract with the club on 27 November 2017.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://ajel.sa/qM526Y/|title=النصر يوقِّع عقدًا احترافيًا مع عبدالإله العمري|website=Ajel.sa|accessdate=27 December 2018|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181227230512/https://ajel.sa/qM526Y/|archive-date=27 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> On 14 December 2017, he made his debut in a 1–1 draw against [[Al-Faisaly FC|Al-Faisaly]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL NASSR VS. AL FAISALY 1 - 1 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2017/12/14/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-nasr-riyadh/al-faysaly-al-majmaah/2683130/}}</ref> On 27 May 2018, Al-Amri was loaned to [[Al-Wehda Club (Mecca)|Al-Wehda]] for the [[2018–19 Al-Wehda Club season|2018–19 season]].<ref>{{cite web|title=مرحباً بكم في نادي #الوحدة|url=https://twitter.com/alwehdaclub1/status/1000939069336182784|publisher=[[Twitter]]|date=21 July 2018}}</ref> Following his return from loan, he was mainly used as a fourth-choice centre-back. However, during the latter half of the 2019–20 season, he managed to establish himself as a starter. He made 15 appearances throughout all competitions. He scored his first goal for the club on 22 February 2020 in a 2–0 win against [[Al-Hazem F.C.|Al-Hazem]].<ref>{{cite web |title=AL HAZM VS. AL NASSR 0 - 2 |url=https://us.soccerway.com/matches/2020/02/22/saudi-arabia/pro-league/al-hazm-rass/al-nasr-riyadh/3202098/}}</ref> On 27 January 2021, Al-Amri renewed his contract with Al-Nassr until the end of the 2023–24 season.<ref>{{cite web |title=النصر يجدد عقد عبدالإله العمري لثلاث سنوات |url=https://www.dawriplus.com/news/51067-%D8%A7%D9%84%D9%86%D8%B5%D8%B1-%D9%8A%D8%AC%D8%AF%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D9%82%D8%AF-%D8%B9%D8%A8%D8%AF%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%A5%D9%84%D9%87-%D8%A7%D9%84%D8%B9%D9%85%D8%B1%D9%8A-%D9%84%D8%AB%D9%84%D8%A7%D8%AB-%D8%B3%D9%86%D9%88%D8%A7%D8%AA.html}}</ref> On 7 December 2023, he renewed his contract with Al-Nassr for a further four years.<ref>{{cite web |title=النصر يجدد عقد عبدالإله العمري |url=https://www.kooora.com/?n=1291089}}</ref> On 1 September 2024, Al-Amri joined [[Al-Ittihad Club (Jeddah)|Al-Ittihad]] on a one-year loan.<ref>{{cite web |title=الاتحاد يضم مدافع النصر "العمري" على سبيل الإعارة حتى نهاية الموسم |date=September 2024 |url=https://sabq.org/sports/ngxpz8pvey}}</ref> He returned to Al-Nassr the following season.

==International career==
Al-Amri has represented Saudi Arabia at [[Saudi Arabia national under-20 football team|under-20 level]] and [[Saudi Arabia national under-23 football team|under-23 level]]. He captained the Saudi Arabia under-20 side at the [[2017 FIFA U-20 World Cup|2017 U-20 World Cup]].

He made his debut for the [[Saudi Arabia national football team|Saudi Arabia national team]] at the [[2019 AFC Asian Cup]].<ref>{{cite web|title=الكشف عن قائمة المنتخب الوطني استعدادا لكأس آسيا 2019 بالإمارات|url=http://www.saff.com.sa/News/Saudi-National-Team/national-team-squad-afc2019|work=[[Saudi Arabian Football Federation|SAFF]]|accessdate=20 December 2018|date=20 December 2018|language=ar|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20181223205603/http://www.saff.com.sa/News/Saudi-National-Team/national-team-squad-afc2019|archive-date=23 December 2018|url-status=dead}}</ref> In July 2021, Al-Amri was named in the squad for the [[Football at the 2020 Summer Olympics – Men's tournament|2020 Olympics]].<ref>{{cite web |title=الشهري يعلن قائمة الأخضر المشاركة في دورة الألعاب الأولمبية طوكيو 2020 |url=https://www.saff.com.sa/news.php?id=931}}</ref> In November 2022, he was named in the squad for the [[2022 FIFA World Cup]].<ref>{{cite web |url=https://www.saff.com.sa/en/news.php?id=1932 |title=Renard announces the national team list for the World Cup 2022 in Qatar |publisher=[[Saudi Arabian Football Federation]] |date=11 November 2022 |access-date=12 November 2022}}</ref>

